    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1855-09-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1855-09-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="149" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d149">
                <head>
                    <seg type="margin">[223]</seg>
                    <hi rend="italic">*Mr. <persName type="from">Gushing</persName>,
                                    Attorney-General, to Mr. <persName type="to">McKeon</persName>,
                                    district attorney.</hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Attorney-General’s
                                    Office</hi>
                    </placeName>,<lb/>
                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1855-09-10">
                        <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 10,
                                    1855</date>.</dateline>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inclose herewith a
                                copy of a dispatch from the British minister to the Secretary of
                                State, and of letters annexed, alleging that troops have been
                                recruited in New York by the Accessory Transit Company for service
                                in the state of Nicaragua, and to request you to investigate the
                                fact, and if, on such investigation, it shall appear that any such
                                recruitments have been made in violation of law, then to institute
                                criminal proceedings against the parties concerned.</p>
                <p>I am, yours, &amp;c., &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>C. CUSHING.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">John McKeon</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Attorney United States, New York.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
